Review the git diff and generate a fun, emoji-rich MR/PR description. Use this format:

## ✨ Summary

[1-3 sentence overview of what this change does and why]

## 🚀 What Changed

- [bulleted list with relevant emojis for each change]

## 🤔 Why Though?

[brief explanation with emojis]

## ✅ Checklist

[Derive specific, emoji-tagged checklist items from the actual diff — things a reviewer should verify or test. Do NOT use generic placeholders. Minimum 2 items. Examples: "- [ ] 🧪 Verify X still passes after Y change", "- [ ] 🔍 Confirm Z behaves correctly".]

## 📝 Notes

[Only include this section if there is genuinely useful extra context — caveats, follow-up work, or trade-offs. Omit it entirely if there is nothing meaningful to add. Never write "N/A".]

Rules:
- Use emojis liberally and appropriately (🐛 for bug fixes, ✨ for new features, 🔧 for config, 🗑️ for deletions, etc.)
- Keep the tone upbeat and fun while still being technically accurate
- Output only the description body — no title line, no preamble
- Never output placeholder text like "N/A" or "[any extra context]"

The git diff may be truncated – focus analysis on visible changes.
